data.value:
This is a program designed to store and track all movies a user owns. It allows the user to add new movies, generating a unique ID to each movie, which can then be used to apply the ID to the actual movie for easy finding. The Movie Library also allows the user to search for a movie, and if found, it selects that movie.
Functionality to still be developed: - Allow the selection of multiple genres per movie - Allow the ability to change genre(s) - Move movies up/down (re-assign ID's accordingly) - Add the ability to select whether a movie is DVD, Blu-Ray, or DVD/Blu-Ray - Add the ability to assign a "borrower" name to a movie, in case someone you know borrows a specific movie
The Movie Library was developed using .NET 4.0 and uses XML to store and retrieve its data.
